 # Color Flipper Application Creation

 ## Create the HTML Structure:
  Create main.html:
    1. Start with the HTML5 doctype declaration: <!DOCTYPE html>.
	2. Add the opening <html> tag with the lang attribute set to "en".

  Inside the <head> section:
    1.Add a <meta charset="UTF-8"> for character encoding.
	2. Add a <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, 3. initial-scale=1.0"> for responsive design.
	3. Add a <title> tag for the application (e.g., <title>Color Flipper</title>).
  Inside the <body> section:
	1. Add a heading using <h3>Color Flipper</h3>.
	2. Create a <div> to hold the buttons.
	3. Add buttons for each color with unique IDs and onclick attributes to call the setColor function.
	4. Add a <div> with an ID of colorDisplay to show the selected color.
	5. Include a <script> tag to link to the index.js file.

  Add CSS Styles:
	1. Inside the <head> section, add a <style> tag.
	2. Define styles for the buttons (e.g., background colors, border radius, width, height, and margin).
	3. Ensure buttons are displayed vertically by setting display: block;.

Create index.js:
	1. Start by creating a constant for the body element: const body = document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0];.
	2. Create a function called setColor(name):
	3. Set the background color of the body based on the name parameter.
	4. Change the text color for readability based on the selected color.
	5. Update the colorDisplay element to show the selected color.
	6. Create a function called randomColor():
	7. Generate random RGB values for red, green, and blue.
	8. Set the background color to the generated color.
	9. Update the colorDisplay element to show the random color.